      "content": "i mean \"short-term disruption\" sounds a bit like an understatement when people are losing their homes. it feels like the bill writers are basically saying coal is just old news and doesn't matter anymore. is there actually any real debate left about whether coal is still a viable part of our energy future, or is it just being phased out because it's seen as \"outdated\"?",
